| Edge Weights               | Algorithm                     |
| -------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| All edges = 1 (unweighted) | ✅ BFS                         |
| Weights ∈ {0,1}            | ✅ 0-1 BFS                     |
| Weights ≥ 0 & single source| ✅ Dijkstra                    |
| Negative weights exist     | ❌ Dijkstra → use Bellman-Ford |
| All-pairs shortest path    | Can use Floyd–Warshall if n is small, otherwise Dijkstra |


The choice of algorithm depends on edge weights, not on whether the graph is directed or undirected.

Dijkstra vs Floyd–Warshall
| Feature                      | Dijkstra                                | Floyd–Warshall                      |
| ---------------------------- | --------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------- |
| **Problem Type**             | Single-source shortest path             | All-pairs shortest path             |
| **Approach**                 | Greedy                                  | Dynamic Programming                 |
| **Core Idea**                | Always pick nearest unvisited node      | Try every node as intermediate      |
| **Time Complexity**          | `O(E log V)` (with heap)                | `O(V³)`                             |
| **Space Complexity**         | `O(V)`                                  | `O(V²)`                             |
| **Graph Type**               | Works best for sparse graphs            | Works fine for dense graphs         |
| **Data Structure**           | Priority Queue (Min Heap)               | 2D matrix                           |
| **Example Use Case**         | GPS routing from one city               | Network latency between all servers |

